      <title>Photograph of Gottfried Galston in the Wilcox &amp; White recording studio</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>Photograph of Gottfried Galston sitting at a recording piano in the Wilcox and White recording studio above the company’s piano/organ factory in Meridien, Connecticut. The piano was used to record the Artrio-Angelus and Voltem rolls for the Wilcox &amp; White player pianos and organs. A handwritten note on the reverse dates this photograph to 1912, which coincides with Galston’s U.S. tour. The photograph is inscribed “With best wishes for a Continental Success, F. C. White &amp; P.K. Wilcox” - probably the two other men in the photograph. Note the photograph of Galston on the wall behind him.</abstract>
